properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 24 at 12:25AM CST until January 24 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Snow Continuing through Friday Morning...

.A slow moving storm system will bring snow to the area tonight
into Friday morning. Light to moderate snow will bring
accumulations of 2 to 4 inches for much of the area, with
isolated 5 inch totals possible. Snow covered roads will continue
through the morning commute.

* WHAT...Snow. Overnight snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches.

* WHERE...Henry IL County.

* WHEN...Until noon CST today.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions will impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Go to www.gettingaroundillinois.com for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY
